<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Morphological description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
The frustule is disciform, valve face concentrically undulate, 13.6-21 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter, striae multiseriate with 9-12 areolae in 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, ribs continue on the curve of a valve, spines grow from each rib (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. SEM (A-E, G, H) and LM images (F) of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city, valve views: A Cyclotella cryptica B Cyclotella marina C, D Cyclotella meduanae E, F Cyclotella meneghiniana G Cyclostephanos dubius H Cyclostephanos invisitatus, with arrows shown on A, D, H marginal and central fultoportulae, B marginal fultoportulae, F central fultoportulae. Scale bars: 2 μm (B, D); 4 μm (A); 5 μm (C, E); 10 μm (F-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545739" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">7G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName authority="Round" authorityName="Round" class="Coscinodiscophyceae" family="Stephanodiscaceae" genus="Cyclostephanos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyclostephanos dubius" order="Thalassiosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Cyclostephanos dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered to be a pelagic taxon, planktonic component of both fresh and brackish lakes (
<bibRefCitation author="Cholnoky, BJ" journalOrPublisher="Cramer Verlag, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B20" refString="Cholnoky, BJ, 1968. Die Oekologie der Diatomeen in Binnengewaessern. Cramer Verlag, Berlin" title="Die Oekologie der Diatomeen in Binnengewaessern." year="1968">Cholnoky 1968</bibRefCitation>
). Often indicating meso- to eutrophic conditions, sometimes recorded for hypertrophic lakes (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02334251" author="Van Dam, H" journalOrPublisher="Netherlands Journal of Aquatic Ecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="117 - 133" refId="B128" refString="Van Dam, H, Mertens, A, Sinkeldam, S, 1994. A coded checklist and ecological indicator values of freshwater diatoms from The Netherlands. Netherlands Journal of Aquatic Ecology 28 (1): 117 - 133, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02334251" title="A coded checklist and ecological indicator values of freshwater diatoms from The Netherlands." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02334251" volume="28" year="1994">Van Dam et al. 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10750-009-9993-4" author="Kirilova, EP" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Applied Phycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B68" refString="Kirilova, EP, Cremer, H, Heiri, O, Lotter, AF, 2010. Eutrophication of moderately deep Dutch lakes during the past century: Flaws in the expectations of water management? Hydrobiologia 637(1): 157-171. https://doi.org/10.1007/s10750-009-9993-4" title="Eutrophication of moderately deep Dutch lakes during the past century: Flaws in the expectations of water management? Hydrobiologia 637 (1): 157 - 171." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10750-009-9993-4" year="2010">Kirilova et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). The species is common in flowing and stagnant water in coastal area, oligosaprobic, alkalibiontic, halophilous &quot;0.0-5 g/dm3&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Hustedt, F" journalOrPublisher="Abhandlungen der Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereine zu Bremen" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="181 - 440" refId="B63" refString="Hustedt, F, 1957. Die Diatomeenflora des Fluss-Systems der Weser im Gebiet der Hansestadt Bremen. Abhandlungen der Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereine zu Bremen 34: 181 - 440" title="Die Diatomeenflora des Fluss-Systems der Weser im Gebiet der Hansestadt Bremen." volume="34" year="1957">Hustedt 1957</bibRefCitation>
); pH value above 7.0 (
<bibRefCitation author="van der Werff, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Vegetation Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B130" refString="van der Werff, A, Huls, H, 1957-1974. Diatomeeenflora van Nederland, afl. 1-10, De Hoef." title="Diatomeeenflora van Nederland, afl. 1 - 10, De Hoef." year="1957 - 1974">van der Werff and Huls 1957-1974</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Foged, N" journalOrPublisher="Meddelelser om Gronland" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 84" refId="B30" refString="Foged, N, 1973. Diatoms from southwest Greenland. Meddelelser om Gronland 194: 1 - 84" title="Diatoms from southwest Greenland." volume="194" year="1973">Foged 1973</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
This species was found above Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River bed (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Species composition of centric diatoms at the investigated sites near Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River in the year 2017 (2013 added for station 2)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" tableUuid="DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677">1</tableCitation>
). From Ukrainian territory, it is known from the Dnipro River, the Dnipro-Bug Estuary (
<bibRefCitation author="Topachevsky, OV" journalOrPublisher="Dumka, Kyiv" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B123" refString="Topachevsky, OV, Oksiyuk, OP, 1960. Vyznacjnyk prisnovodnykh vodorostey Ukrainskoi RSR [Identification manual of freshwater algae of Ukrainian SSR]. 11. Diatomovi vodorosti - Bacillariophyta (Diatomeae). Nauk. Dumka, Kyiv" title="Vyznacjnyk prisnovodnykh vodorostey Ukrainskoi RSR [Identification manual of freshwater algae of Ukrainian SSR]. 11. Diatomovi vodorosti - Bacillariophyta (Diatomeae). Nauk." year="1960">Topachevsky and Oksiyuk 1960</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vladimirova, KS" journalOrPublisher="Studia Botanica Hungarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B132" refString="Vladimirova, KS, 1971. To the problem of study of benthic algae of the Dnipro-Bug estuary. Dniprovsko-Bugskyi liman [The Dnipro-Bug estuary]. Nauk. Dumka, Kyiv, 155-202." title="To the problem of study of benthic algae of the Dnipro-Bug estuary. Dniprovsko-Bugskyi liman [The Dnipro-Bug estuary]. Nauk. Dumka, Kyiv, 155 - 202." year="1971">Vladimirova 1971</bibRefCitation>
) and the Danube River (
<bibRefCitation author="Tsarenko, PM" journalOrPublisher="Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B127" refString="Tsarenko, PM, Wasser, SP, Nevo, E, 2009. Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A.R.A. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" title="Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A. R. A." year="2009">Tsarenko et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName authority="Round" authorityName="Round" class="Coscinodiscophyceae" family="Stephanodiscaceae" genus="Cyclostephanos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyclostephanos dubius" order="Thalassiosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Cyclostephanos dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a cosmopolitan species, recorded for Berlin, Germany (
<bibRefCitation author="Geissler, U" journalOrPublisher="Beiheft" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 777" refId="B35" refString="Geissler, U, Kies, L, 2003. Artendiversitaet und Veraenderungen in der Algenflora zweier staedtischer Ballungsgebiete Deutschlands: Berlin und Hamburg (Diversity and dynamics of the freshwater algal flora in two urban areas of Germany: Berlin and Hamburg). Nova Hedwigia. Beiheft 126: 1 - 777" title="Artendiversitaet und Veraenderungen in der Algenflora zweier staedtischer Ballungsgebiete Deutschlands: Berlin und Hamburg (Diversity and dynamics of the freshwater algal flora in two urban areas of Germany: Berlin and Hamburg). Nova Hedwigia." volume="126" year="2003">Geissler and Kies 2003</bibRefCitation>
) and further sites in Europe (Hungary, Dania, Estonia, Moldova, Russia, Ukraine), Asia (Georgia, Russia, Uzbekistan), North America (Canada, USA), Africa (Egypt); Baltic and White Seas (
<bibRefCitation author="Tsarenko, PM" journalOrPublisher="Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B127" refString="Tsarenko, PM, Wasser, SP, Nevo, E, 2009. Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A.R.A. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" title="Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A. R. A." year="2009">Tsarenko et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2478/v10184-011-0067-0" author="Kiss, KT" journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Croatica" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="311 - 363" refId="B69" refString="Kiss, KT, Klee, R, Ector, L, Acs, E, 2012. Centric diatoms of large rivers and tributaries in Hungary: Morphology and biogeographic distribution. Acta Botanica Croatica 71 (2): 311 - 363, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2478/v10184-011-0067-0" title="Centric diatoms of large rivers and tributaries in Hungary: Morphology and biogeographic distribution." url="https://doi.org/10.2478/v10184-011-0067-0" volume="71" year="2012">Kiss et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Filigran, Yaroslavl" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B45" refString="Genkal, SI, Kulikovskiy, MS, Kuznetsova, IV, 2020. Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]. Filigran, Yaroslavl" title="Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]." year="2020">Genkal et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
